snippet.textDisplay:
I believe that this is a clear representation of Ronnie's constant struggle with overall addiction. Not just because it's a revamp of his song from about a decade ago, but that it seems to still be relevant to him during this day and age. The woman is his addiction personified, with her still looking him in the face during key scenes. "I opened up to see death staring in my face." She also has 4 individual dancers that seem to praise her by dancing around her in ritualistic fashion. Given the number of them, I believe they could be the 4 horsemen of Ronnie's apocalypse. He has two separate songs titled as such; My Apocalypse (II) which shows that she would be the end to him if he would continue their relationship, or think to go back and flirt with. "The feel of mortal stalking still reverberates. Everywhere I go I bring this coffin just in case."

Can't you see?

snippet.textDisplay: This song came out nine years ago. I remember listening to it with my first girlfriend. Since then I’ve been in two highly toxic relationships back to back. I never really paid much attention to the lyrics until today. It’s all about toxic people, losing yourself in those relationships, becoming toxic, but being self aware to get out of them and find yourself again. This reimagining is about the same thing. Except once the smoke has cleared , you’ve ran from your past, and those people are long gone. The haunting of it is still there and you’re faced with one last person that you need to confront. Yourself..
